Vercel Speed Insights Installation

Successfully installed and configured Vercel Speed Insights for this React + Vite project.

## Changes Made:

### 1. Package Installation
- Installed `@vercel/speed-insights@^2.0.0` package using npm
- Updated `package.json` to include the new dependency
- Updated `package-lock.json` with the new dependency tree (227 packages added)

### 2. Code Integration
Modified `src/App.tsx`:
- Added import statement: `import { SpeedInsights } from "@vercel/speed-insights/react";`
- Added `<SpeedInsights />` component inside the BrowserRouter, at the root level of the app
- Placement ensures Speed Insights tracks all routes and navigation events

### 3. Implementation Details
- Followed official Vercel documentation from https://vercel.com/docs/speed-insights/quickstart
- Used React-specific integration as per the documentation for React + Vite projects
- Component is placed at the app root level to capture metrics across all pages
- No additional configuration required - the component works out of the box

### 4. Verification
- Build completed successfully with no errors
- Linting passed for the modified App.tsx file (pre-existing linting issues in other files are unrelated)
- No new TypeScript errors introduced
- All changes follow existing code patterns and conventions

## Next Steps:
To enable Speed Insights data collection on Vercel:
1. Deploy this application to Vercel
2. Navigate to the Vercel dashboard
3. Select Speed Insights from the sidebar
4. Choose this project and click "Enable"
5. After the next deployment, metrics will start being collected at `/_vercel/speed-insights/*`

The implementation is complete and ready for deployment.
